        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued June 28 at 3:31PM EDT until June 28 at 4:00PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 331 PM EDT, a severe thunderstorm was located near Downtown
Asheville, or near North Asheville, and is nearly stationary.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and quarter size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vehicles is expected. Expect wind
damage to trees and power lines.

Locations impacted include...
Downtown Asheville, East Asheville, West Asheville, North Asheville,
Woodfin, Weaverville, UNC-Asheville, and Biltmore Forest.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
